About Me

Where healthcare meets cutting-edge AI

Healthcare AI Engineer with a Mission

I'm a unique blend of healthcare professional and AI software engineer. Currently pursuing Biomedical Sciences at USF (4.0 GPA) while researching machine learning applications at Moffitt Cancer Center, I bring hands-on clinical experience to every line of code I write.

My journey combines Computer Science (UCF, 3.85 GPA, Cum Laude) with real-world healthcare work at HCA Florida, giving me the rare ability to understand both the technical challenges and clinical realities of health tech solutions.

I'm currently building BayFlowHealth.AI - streamlining Revenue Cycle Management for hospitals and clinics through intelligent automation.
